(9487, 287, 'flexible_content_1_content_area_content', 'IFFCO has set the following key focus areas to guide us in achieving the goals. We are confident that focusing our efforts into these areas will lead to progress towards the goals and also allow us to establish the right partnership to create scalable impacts. Moving forward, IFFCO will report progress against the following key focus areas and milestones under the Sustainability Dashboard.\r\n<h3>Traceability</h3>\r\nIFFCO does not own or operate any upstream assets such as oil palm plantations and mills, thus 00% of the palm oil materials come from third party supplying mills, thus 00% of the palm oil materials come from third party supplying mills, refineries or aggregators. a slightly more than 50% of our sourced palm oil that we further process in one of our refineries in Middle East, North africa and South asia come from tier external refineries or aggregators. Nearly 50% of the remaining sourced palm oil volumes come from our Indonesia based refinery that sources and processes palm oil directly from mills. IFFCO’s traceability action plans include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Establishing IFFCO’s global palm footprint to understand the palm oil supply origin.</li>\r\n 	<li>Working with suppliers on traceability to mill and map the supply base to achieve traceability to plantations.</li>\r\n 	<li>analysing the risks and best practices\' in our supply base.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIFFCO’s milestone is to maintain full traceability of our palm - based products to supplying mills that we have achieved since 09, and to work with our suppliers to achieve full traceability to plantation for palm oil tht we directly source from palm oil mills by end-03 and for indirectly source by end-07.'),
